42@interface WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder : NSObject
43- (instancetype)initWithCodecInfo:(RTCVideoCodecInfo*)codecInfo;
44- (webrtc::VideoCodecType)codecType;
45- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoEncoderCallback)callback;
46- (NSInteger)releaseEncoder;
47- (NSInteger)startEncodeWithSettings:(RTCVideoEncoderSettings *)settings numberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores;
48- (NSInteger)encode:(RTCVideoFrame *)frame codecSpecificInfo:(nullable id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)info frameTypes:(NSArray<NSNumber *> *)frameTypes;
49- (int)setBitrate:(uint32_t)bitrateKbit framerate:(uint32_t)framerate;
50- (void)setLowLatency:(bool)lowLatencyEnabled;
51@end
52
53@implementation WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder {
54 RTCVideoEncoderH264 *m_h264Encoder;
55 RTCVideoEncoderH265 *m_h265Encoder;
56}
57
58- (instancetype)initWithCodecInfo:(RTCVideoCodecInfo*)codecInfo {
59 if (self = [super init]) {
60 if ([codecInfo.name isEqualToString:@"H265"])
61 m_h265Encoder = [[RTCVideoEncoderH265 alloc] initWithCodecInfo:codecInfo];
62 else
63 m_h264Encoder = [[RTCVideoEncoderH264 alloc] initWithCodecInfo:codecInfo];
64 }
65 return self;
66}
67
68- (webrtc::VideoCodecType)codecType
69{
70 if (m_h264Encoder)
71 return webrtc::kVideoCodecH264;
72 return webrtc::kVideoCodecH265;
73}
74
75- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoEncoderCallback)callback {
76 if (m_h264Encoder)
77 return [m_h264Encoder setCallback:callback];
78 return [m_h265Encoder setCallback:callback];
79}
80
81- (NSInteger)releaseEncoder {
82 if (m_h264Encoder)
83 return [m_h264Encoder releaseEncoder];
84 return [m_h265Encoder releaseEncoder];
85}
86
87- (NSInteger)startEncodeWithSettings:(RTCVideoEncoderSettings *)settings numberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores {
88 if (m_h264Encoder)
89 return [m_h264Encoder startEncodeWithSettings:settings numberOfCores:numberOfCores];
90 return [m_h265Encoder startEncodeWithSettings:settings numberOfCores:numberOfCores];
91}
92
93- (NSInteger)encode:(RTCVideoFrame *)frame codecSpecificInfo:(nullable id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)info frameTypes:(NSArray<NSNumber *> *)frameTypes {
94 if (m_h264Encoder)
95 return [m_h264Encoder encode:frame codecSpecificInfo:info frameTypes:frameTypes];
96 return [m_h265Encoder encode:frame codecSpecificInfo:info frameTypes:frameTypes];
97}
98
99- (int)setBitrate:(uint32_t)bitrateKbit framerate:(uint32_t)framerate {
100 if (m_h264Encoder)
101 return [m_h264Encoder setBitrate:bitrateKbit framerate:framerate];
102 return [m_h265Encoder setBitrate:bitrateKbit framerate:framerate];
103}
104- (void)setLowLatency:(bool)lowLatencyEnabled {
105 if (m_h264Encoder)
106 [m_h264Encoder setH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled:lowLatencyEnabled];
107}
108@end

112class VideoEncoderFactoryWithSimulcast final : public VideoEncoderFactory {
113public:
114 explicit VideoEncoderFactoryWithSimulcast(std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoderFactory>&& factory)
115 : m_internalEncoderFactory(std::move(factory))
116 {
117 }
118
119 VideoEncoderFactory::CodecInfo QueryVideoEncoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format) const final { return m_internalEncoderFactory->QueryVideoEncoder(format); }
120 std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> CreateVideoEncoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format) final;
121 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> GetSupportedFormats() const final { return m_internalEncoderFactory->GetSupportedFormats(); }
122
123private:
124 const std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoderFactory> m_internalEncoderFactory;
125};

143struct VideoEncoderCallbacks {
144 VideoEncoderCreateCallback createCallback;
145 VideoEncoderReleaseCallback releaseCallback;
146 VideoEncoderInitializeCallback initializeCallback;
147 VideoEncoderEncodeCallback encodeCallback;
148 VideoEncoderRegisterEncodeCompleteCallback registerEncodeCompleteCallback;
149 VideoEncoderSetRatesCallback setRatesCallback;
150};
151
152static VideoEncoderCallbacks& videoEncoderCallbacks() {
153 static VideoEncoderCallbacks callbacks;
154 return callbacks;
155}
156
157void setVideoEncoderCallbacks(VideoEncoderCreateCallback createCallback, VideoEncoderReleaseCallback releaseCallback, VideoEncoderInitializeCallback initializeCallback, VideoEncoderEncodeCallback encodeCallback, VideoEncoderRegisterEncodeCompleteCallback registerEncodeCompleteCallback, VideoEncoderSetRatesCallback setRatesCallback)
158{
159 auto& callbacks = videoEncoderCallbacks();
160 callbacks.createCallback = createCallback;
161 callbacks.releaseCallback = releaseCallback;
162 callbacks.initializeCallback = initializeCallback;
163 callbacks.encodeCallback = encodeCallback;
164 callbacks.registerEncodeCompleteCallback = registerEncodeCompleteCallback;
165 callbacks.setRatesCallback = setRatesCallback;
166}

168class RemoteVideoEncoder final : public webrtc::VideoEncoder {
169public:
170 explicit RemoteVideoEncoder(WebKitVideoEncoder);
171 ~RemoteVideoEncoder();
172
173private:
174 int32_t InitEncode(const VideoCodec*, const Settings&) final;
175 int32_t RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(EncodedImageCallback*) final;
176 int32_t Release() final;
177 int32_t Encode(const VideoFrame&, const std::vector<VideoFrameType>*) final;
178 void SetRates(const RateControlParameters&) final;
179 EncoderInfo GetEncoderInfo() const final;
180
181 WebKitVideoEncoder m_internalEncoder;
182};
183
184class RemoteVideoEncoderFactory final : public VideoEncoderFactory {
185public:
186 explicit RemoteVideoEncoderFactory(std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoderFactory>&&);
187 ~RemoteVideoEncoderFactory() = default;
188
189private:
190 VideoEncoderFactory::CodecInfo QueryVideoEncoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format) const final { return m_internalFactory->QueryVideoEncoder(format); }
191 std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> CreateVideoEncoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format) final;
192 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> GetSupportedFormats() const final { return m_internalFactory->GetSupportedFormats(); }
193
194 std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoderFactory> m_internalFactory;
195};
196
197RemoteVideoEncoderFactory::RemoteVideoEncoderFactory(std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoderFactory>&& factory)
198 : m_internalFactory(std::move(factory))
199{
200}
201
202std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> RemoteVideoEncoderFactory::CreateVideoEncoder(const SdpVideoFormat& format)
203{
204 if (!videoEncoderCallbacks().createCallback)
205 return m_internalFactory->CreateVideoEncoder(format);
206
207 auto internalEncoder = videoEncoderCallbacks().createCallback(format);
208 if (!internalEncoder)
209 return m_internalFactory->CreateVideoEncoder(format);
210
211 return std::make_unique<RemoteVideoEncoder>(internalEncoder);
212}
213
214std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoderFactory> createWebKitEncoderFactory(WebKitH265 supportsH265, WebKitVP9 supportsVP9, WebKitH264LowLatency useH264LowLatency)
215{
216#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER || ENABLE_VCP_VTB_ENCODER
217 static std::once_flag onceFlag;
218 std::call_once(onceFlag, [] {
219 webrtc::VPModuleInitialize();
220 });
221#endif
222
223 auto internalFactory = ObjCToNativeVideoEncoderFactory([[RTCDefaultVideoEncoderFactory alloc] initWithH265: supportsH265 == WebKitH265::On vp9Profile0:supportsVP9 > WebKitVP9::Off vp9Profile2:supportsVP9 == WebKitVP9::Profile0And2 lowLatencyH264:useH264LowLatency == WebKitH264LowLatency::On]);
224
225 return std::make_unique<VideoEncoderFactoryWithSimulcast>(std::make_unique<RemoteVideoEncoderFactory>(std::move(internalFactory)));
226}

231}

237
238int32_t RemoteVideoEncoder::InitEncode(const VideoCodec* codec, const Settings&)
239{
240 if (SimulcastUtility::NumberOfSimulcastStreams(*codec) > 1)
241 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_SIMULCAST_PARAMETERS_NOT_SUPPORTED;
242
243 return videoEncoderCallbacks().initializeCallback(m_internalEncoder, *codec);
244}
245
246int32_t RemoteVideoEncoder::Release()
247{
248 RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(nullptr);
249 return 0;
250}
251
252int32_t RemoteVideoEncoder::Encode(const VideoFrame& frame, const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frameTypes)
253{
254 bool shouldEncodeKeyFrame = false;
255 for (size_t i = 0; i < frameTypes->size(); ++i) {
256 if (frameTypes->at(i) == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
257 shouldEncodeKeyFrame = true;
258 break;
259 }
260 }
261
262 return videoEncoderCallbacks().encodeCallback(m_internalEncoder, frame, shouldEncodeKeyFrame);
263}
264
265void RemoteVideoEncoder::SetRates(const RateControlParameters& rates)
266{
267 videoEncoderCallbacks().setRatesCallback(m_internalEncoder, rates);
268}
269
270RemoteVideoEncoder::EncoderInfo RemoteVideoEncoder::GetEncoderInfo() const
271{
272 EncoderInfo info;
273 info.supports_native_handle = true;
274 info.implementation_name = "RemoteVideoToolBox";
275 info.is_hardware_accelerated = true;
276 info.has_internal_source = false;
277
278 // Values taken from RTCVideoEncoderH264.mm
279 const int kLowH264QpThreshold = 28;
280 const int kHighH264QpThreshold = 39;
281 info.scaling_settings = ScalingSettings(kLowH264QpThreshold, kHighH264QpThreshold);
282
283 return info;
284}
285
286int32_t RemoteVideoEncoder::RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(EncodedImageCallback* callback)
287{
288 return videoEncoderCallbacks().registerEncodeCompleteCallback(m_internalEncoder, callback);
289}
290
291void encoderVideoTaskComplete(void* callback, webrtc::VideoCodecType codecType, const uint8_t* buffer, size_t length, const WebKitEncodedFrameInfo& info)
292{
293 webrtc::EncodedImage encodedImage;
294 encodedImage.SetEncodedData(EncodedImageBuffer::Create(buffer, length));
295
296 encodedImage._encodedWidth = info.width;
297 encodedImage._encodedHeight = info.height;
298 encodedImage.SetTimestamp(info.timeStamp);
299 encodedImage.capture_time_ms_ = info.captureTimeMS;
300 encodedImage.ntp_time_ms_ = info.ntpTimeMS;
301 encodedImage.timing_ = info.timing;
302 encodedImage._frameType = info.frameType;
303 encodedImage.rotation_ = info.rotation;
304 encodedImage.qp_ = info.qp;
305 encodedImage.content_type_ = info.contentType;
306
307 CodecSpecificInfo codecSpecificInfo;
308 codecSpecificInfo.codecType = codecType;
309 if (codecType == kVideoCodecH264)
310 codecSpecificInfo.codecSpecific.H264.packetization_mode = H264PacketizationMode::NonInterleaved;
311 else if (codecType == kVideoCodecH265)
312 codecSpecificInfo.codecSpecific.H265.packetization_mode = H265PacketizationMode::NonInterleaved;
313
314 static_cast<EncodedImageCallback*>(callback)->OnEncodedImage(encodedImage, &codecSpecificInfo);
315}
316
317void* createLocalEncoder(const webrtc::SdpVideoFormat& format, LocalEncoderCallback callback)
318{
319 auto *codecInfo = [[RTCVideoCodecInfo alloc] initWithNativeSdpVideoFormat: format];
320 auto *encoder = [[WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder alloc] initWithCodecInfo:codecInfo];
321
322 [encoder setCallback:^BOOL(RTCEncodedImage *_Nonnull frame, id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo> _Nonnull codecSpecificInfo, RTCRtpFragmentationHeader * _Nullable header) {
323 EncodedImage encodedImage = [frame nativeEncodedImage];
324
325 WebKitEncodedFrameInfo info;
326 info.width = encodedImage._encodedWidth;
327 info.height = encodedImage._encodedHeight;
328 info.timeStamp = encodedImage.Timestamp();
329 info.ntpTimeMS = encodedImage.ntp_time_ms_;
330 info.captureTimeMS = encodedImage.capture_time_ms_;
331 info.frameType = encodedImage._frameType;
332 info.rotation = encodedImage.rotation_;
333 info.contentType = encodedImage.content_type_;
334 info.qp = encodedImage.qp_;
335 info.timing = encodedImage.timing_;
336
337 callback(encodedImage.data(), encodedImage.size(), info);
338 return YES;
339 }];
340
341 return (__bridge_retained void*)encoder;
342
343}
344
345void releaseLocalEncoder(LocalEncoder localEncoder)
346{
347 auto *encoder = (__bridge_transfer WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder *)(localEncoder);
348 [encoder releaseEncoder];
349}
350
351void initializeLocalEncoder(LocalEncoder localEncoder, uint16_t width, uint16_t height, unsigned int startBitrate, unsigned int maxBitrate, unsigned int minBitrate, uint32_t maxFramerate)
352{
353 auto *encoder = (__bridge WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder *)(localEncoder);
354
355 webrtc::VideoCodec codecSettings;
356 codecSettings.width = width;
357 codecSettings.height = height;
358 codecSettings.startBitrate = startBitrate;
359 codecSettings.maxBitrate = maxBitrate;
360 codecSettings.minBitrate = minBitrate;
361 codecSettings.maxFramerate = maxFramerate;
362 codecSettings.codecType = encoder.codecType;
363
364 [encoder startEncodeWithSettings:[[RTCVideoEncoderSettings alloc] initWithNativeVideoCodec:&codecSettings] numberOfCores:1];
365}
366
367void encodeLocalEncoderFrame(LocalEncoder localEncoder, CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer, int64_t timeStampNs, uint32_t timeStamp, webrtc::VideoRotation rotation, bool isKeyframeRequired)
368{
369 NSMutableArray<NSNumber *> *rtcFrameTypes = [NSMutableArray array];
370 if (isKeyframeRequired)
371 [rtcFrameTypes addObject:@(RTCFrameType(RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey))];
372
373 auto *videoFrame = [[RTCVideoFrame alloc] initWithBuffer:ToObjCVideoFrameBuffer(pixelBufferToFrame(pixelBuffer)) rotation:RTCVideoRotation(rotation) timeStampNs:timeStampNs];
374 videoFrame.timeStamp = timeStamp;
375 auto *encoder = (__bridge WK_RTCLocalVideoH264H265Encoder *)(localEncoder);
376 [encoder encode:videoFrame codecSpecificInfo:nil frameTypes:rtcFrameTypes];
377}

383}

389}
